folder: Androvette Street & Kreischer Street, Staten Island, NY
text:
Androvette Street, south side, west from Kreischer Street, showing the rears of houses. These were, in all likelihood,the homes of the workmen of the Kreischer Brick Company factory, which was nearby. On the extreme, right at the N.W. corner of Kreischer Street, is the old Neilsen's Hotel, later known as the Four Corners House.

May 3, 1937

P. L. Sperr

folder: Kreischer Street & Androvette Street, Staten Island, NY
text:
Kreischer Street, south from Androvette Street. In the right background appears part of the Outerbridge Crossing.

May 3, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
